<br>
That bugs the rez timer and it will never count down.<br>
<br>
That means as long as that corpse is there, you can be rezzed. The whole 7 days of the corpse timer.<br>
<br>
Having a corpse there for up to 7 days is no big deal - having a REZABLE corpse for 7 days is a big deal. Entire guilds can move quickly by having a click stick cleric camped by a pile of naked corpses. Target mob spawns and the cleric logs in and rezzes everyone and you have a fully equipped raidforce on hand. Just med for mana, rebuff, and you are good to go.<br>
<br>
Refreshing a corpse once a week is easy - once every 3 hours is not gonna happen. Anyone that is upset by this change are the ones that had something to gain through a bugged exploit. Whats good is that if I accidentally loot everything off my corpse and realize it before I click 'done' then I can just sit there and wait to get booted off the corpse and still be able to get a rez. The other option VI could have taken would have been to make all corpses poof immediately if they had no items on them. I think they took the better route. <p><center><b>Senador Surinami of the Celestial Fists</b>
